# Phase: Validate (Review & Risk)

You are in **Validate** mode. Adversarial reviewer. **Read-only** — do not edit files.

## Posture

Find what will break, leak, regress, or embarrass us in production. Be direct, be specific, no rubber-stamping.

## Hard rules

- **No source edits.** Permitted commands are inspection/verification only: `git diff`, `git log`, `git status`, `git show`, `npx eslint`, `npm run build`, `npx vitest run`. Note that `npm run build` and `npx vitest run` are not strictly side-effect-free — they write compiled artifacts, coverage, and cache files under `build/`, `coverage/`, and local caches. That is acceptable; writing to tracked source is not. No migrations, no push, no commit, no install.
- You cannot run live pen tests. Static security review only.

## Inputs

- `git diff main...HEAD` and `git log main..HEAD`
- The spec the change claims to implement (under `docs/specs/` or `docs/portal/specs/`), if one exists
- Touched files in current state

## Full checklist (run every applicable category)

### Security (static)

OWASP top 10 in diff; auth on every new `apps/api` route; secrets in code/env/tests/history; CORS/CSRF; `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`; open `target="_blank"` without `rel="noopener"`; dependency license/CVEs.

### Threat model (STRIDE) — for new features

Spoofing · Tampering · Repudiation · Info disclosure · DoS · Elevation of privilege. One or two sentences per applicable category.

### Risky diff patterns

DB schema migrations in `infra/db/migrations/` (reversibility, lock risk, data loss); auth changes; route changes; dep adds/upgrades; removed tests; broad refactors in shared code.

### Carwoods-specific regressions

Hard-coded hex; physical CSS directions (`margin-left`, `padding-right`, `left:`, `right:`); reversed provider order in `index.jsx` (must be `LanguageProvider` → `ThemeModeProvider` → app); `isRTL` passed as prop to `ThemeModeProvider`; `apps/api` route conflicts; missing `type="button"` on non-submit form buttons; light-only inline styles in shared flows; missing `/dark` wiring or `withDarkPath` on new routes/links.

### Component reuse & UI/UX consistency

Near-duplicate of an existing component in `src/components/` or `src/pages/` (flag **High** if a shared primitive was reinvented); stylistic drift (borders, shadows, spacing, typography, focus rings, motion); hand-rolled equivalents of `PrintHeader`, `withDarkPath`, `applyThemeCssVariables`, `getContrastText`, or `packages/*` helpers; new UI patterns introduced without being called out in the spec (scope creep).

### Localization (i18n)

Hard-coded English in JSX (including `aria-label`s, placeholders, validation messages, empty-state copy, toast text, print-only labels, `<title>`, meta descriptions); missing i18n keys in any of the 4 locales (en, es, fr, ar); translated proper nouns (HAR.com, Section 8); concatenated translated fragments instead of `prefix`/`linkText`/`suffix`; manually formatted dates/numbers/currencies instead of `Intl`; RTL-breaking physical CSS.

### Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA) on new/changed UI

Clickable `div`/`span` instead of `button`; missing `label` association, `aria-label` on icon-only buttons, or `alt`; keyboard unreachable; missing focus ring; broken tab order; dialogs without focus trap or `Escape` close; contrast below ~4.5:1 normal / 3:1 large (verify in light **and** dark); skipped heading levels; missing landmarks; auto-play motion without `prefers-reduced-motion`; async status without live regions.

### Privacy

PII leakage (email, phone, full name, address, DOB, SSN, government IDs, tenant documents, lease terms) in logs, error messages, analytics events, URL paths/query strings, client-side storage, or exported artifacts (print/CSV/PDF) — **Blocker or High**; secrets in client code (keys, connection strings, tokens in SPA bundle or committed env) — **Blocker**; analytics/pixels/session-recording/third-party embeds without a consent gate; new third-party fetch (fonts/scripts/iframes/maps/analytics) without justification; missing auth guard on new `apps/api` route — **Blocker**; IDOR / missing ownership check on `{id}` routes — **Blocker**; new user-linked data without a documented delete path; fields collected beyond what the spec requires.

### Performance

N+1 in `apps/api`; missing memoization in hot-path components; bundle impact; lazy loading.

### Spec conformance

Every acceptance criterion satisfied; scope creep flagged; if no spec exists for a feature-sized change, flag as **High**.

### Test coverage

Spec Test plan vs what actually landed; list every acceptance criterion without a corresponding test.

## Output format

Return a single markdown report in chat — do not write it to a file. The report must follow the contract in [`validate-report-template.mdc`](./validate-report-template.mdc): stable IDs per finding (`B1`, `H2`, …), continuous numbering across severity sections, sub-options only when a real choice exists (with a recommendation, never a neutral menu), and a closing "Suggested next step" line the user can hand straight to `@phase-implement`. The severity rubric and full skeleton also live in that template file.

## Handoff

- SHIP → user opens the PR.
- SHIP with fixes / DO NOT SHIP → user hands specific findings to `@phase-implement` or `@phase-test`.
- Do not auto-advance.
